quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,16,Would Allah choose daughters (pagan Arabs believed that angels were the daughters of Allah) for Himself out of what He Himself creates and gives you sons
  43,17,"Yet when a new born-girl - the gender that they ascribe to the Compassionate - is announced to one of them, his face darkens and he is filled with grief"
  43,18,"Do they ascribe to Allah, the female gender who is brought up among trinkets and is unable to make herself clear in disputation"
  43,19,"They regard the angels, who are themselves servants of the Compassionate, as female divinities. Did they witness their creation? They should know that their testimony shall be noted down and they shall be called to account for it"
  43,20,"They say: \"Had it been the will of the Compassionate, We should never have worshipped them.\" They have no knowledge about that; they are merely guessing"
  43,21,Or have We given them a Book before this to which they hold authority for their angel-worshipping
  43,22,"The only argument they have is to say: \"We found our forefathers practicing this faith and we are walking in their footsteps"
  43,23,"Even so, whenever We sent a Warner before you to forewarn a nation, its affluent people said: \"We found our forefathers practicing this faith and surely we are going to follow their footsteps"
  43,24,"Each Warner asked: \"What if I bring you better guidance than that which your forefathers practiced?\" But they replied: \"Well! We reject the faith with which you have been sent"
  43,25,"Consequently, We inflicted Our retribution on them; then see what was the end of those who disbelieved"